Complainant/ Guardian:
Chavez did not speak English. Communication was completed through an Interpreter from Carroll County Public Schools, Nicole Leanna Fuentes (DOB: 6/10/1972, W/F). Chavez stated that he last saw Baltazar Gordian Chavez (DOB: 9/1/2007, H/M) on Sunday, March 19, 2023 at approximately 2300 hours and when he woke up at approximately 0600 hours on March 20, 2023 he was not there anymore. Chavez is the brother/ guardian of Baltazar. Baltazar just immigrated to the US recently from Guatemala. Baltazar is suspected to have left with a black backpack with some of his clothes in it. Baltazar did not take his phone with him. Chavez advised that Century High School contacted him on 3/20/2023 because Baltazar was not in school. Chavez informed the school that he did not know where Baltazar was. Chavez stated that Baltazar does not want to go to school and that he only wants to work. Chavez added that Baltazar contacted his father, who still lives in Guatemala approximately one week ago, and told him that he has friends who live in Miami, FL. Chavez did not have anymore information regarding the conversation and he does not know who those friends are. Chavez does not believe that Baltazar would go back to Guatemala.
Baltazar is 15 years old Hispanic male. He is approximately 5’9” tall and weighs approximately 150lbs. He has black hair and brown eyes. Baltazar does not have facial hair and his hair length is average. He is a 9th grader at Century High School.

Interpreter from Carroll County Public Schools Statement:
Made contact with Ana Gordian Chavez (DOB: 9/1/2007, H/F) via phone on the morning of 3/21/2023, and Ana informed her that Baltazar was not with her.

Narrative:
On 3/21/2023 at approximately 1226 hours I was dispatched to 1209 Liberty Rd, Apt 219, Eldersburg, MD 21074 for the report of a missing person. Upon my arrival I met with Sebastian Gordian Chavez (DOB: 5/19/1997, H/M) communication with Chavez was completed through an Interpreter from Carroll County Public Schools, Nicole Leanna Fuentes (DOB: 6/10/1972, W/F).
Baltazar was previously reported missing on 2/14/2023 and located working at 822 N. Rolling Rd, Catonsville, MD 21228. Baltazar was also known to be staying at 6319 Monika Pl, Apt 205, Woodlawn, MD 21043, with his sister, Ana Gordian Chavez (DOB: 9/1/2007, H/F).
Maryland State Police Golden Ring Barrack is responding to 822 N. Rolling Rd, Catonsville, MD 21228 to attempt to locate Baltazar if he is working.
Baltazar Gordian Chavez (DOB: 9/1/2007, H/M) was entered into NCIC as a missing person, NCIC# M367222552 and a recent photograph of Baltazar was attached.
All events occurred in Carroll County, MD.
Case Open.

12 Hour Follow-up

On Wednesday, March 22, 2023 at approximately 0300 hours, TFC Nield #6851, responded to 1209 Liberty Rd, Apt 219, Eldersburg, MD 21784 to conduct a 12 hour follow-up interview.  TFC Nield contacted the complainant, Sebastian Gordian Chavez, who advised TFC Nield that the missing person, Baltazar Gordian Chavez, had not returned home and had not been seen or heard from since the initial report was filed.  Sebastian Gordian Chavez was advised to contact MSP Westminster should Baltazar return, make contact or his whereabouts become known.  

CASE REMAINS OPEN.

Narrative:
On 3/22/2023 Deputy Harvey of the Carroll County Sheriff's Office, School Resource Officer of Century High School, advised that Baltazar was absent at school.
On 3/22/2023 at approximately 1220 hours Trooper Rhoten of the Maryland State Police Golden Ring Barrack responded to 6319 Monika Place, Apt. 205, Woodlawn, MD and made contact with Ana (Baltazar's sister) and Benito Darwin Raymundo Gallego (DOB: 7/27/2004, H/M). Neither party admitted to knowing where Baltazar is, however when Trooper Rhoten asked to look around the apartment they would not allow him to do so.
Trooper Rhoten also responded to 822 Rolling Rd, Catonsville, MD Be-Se-To Korean Seoul Restaurant to inquire about Baltazar's whereabouts. Trooper Rhoten made contact with the owner of the restaurant, Wounghee Hill. Trooper Rhoten showed Hill a photograph of Baltazar and Hill advised that he does not know Baltazar and had never seen him before.   

Case remains open.

NARRATIVE:

On Friday, May 26, 2023, TFC Frye #7198 responded to 1209 Liberty Rd, Apt 219, Eldersburg, MD 21784 in an attempt to contact the complainant, Sebastian Chavez, or the MPR, Baltazar Chavez.  There was no answer at the door and no contact was able to be made with anyone on premise.  I attempted to contact the complainant by telephone but it went to voice mail.  

CASE OPEN.

Narrative:

      On May 30, 2023, I, Cpl. Theodore Buck of the Maryland State Police Criminal Enforcement Division was contacted by MSP Westminster Barrack D/Sgt Petras about this case.  I was requested to take over the investigation due to the juvenile being missing for an extended period of time.  The missing juvenile was identified as Baltazar Gordian Chavez (information above).  I was advised this was not the first time Baltazar had run away (previous case 2/14/2023) and that he was previously found at the restaurant he works (worked) at.  It should be noted that the initial Trooper advised in his report that Troopers did contact the employer about this case, who advised that he did not know who Baltazar was.  Additionally, contact was made with Baltazar's sister, who stated she had not seen her brother.  She would not let Law Enforcement in to check her property.
  • Last known work address: 822 N. Rolling Rd, Catonsville, MD 21228.
  • Sister - Ana Gordian Chavez (DOB: 9/1/2007, H/F) - 6319 Monika Pl, Apt 205, Woodlawn, MD 21043.

      On May 31, 2023, I conducted a phone interview with the complainant in this case.  I was assisted by Nicole Fuentes, who is an interpreter with Carroll County Public Schools.  During the interview, the complainant advised that he had no immediate concerns for his brother's safety.  The complainant was specifically asked if this could have anything to do with his brother recently coming across the border illegally, to which he advised no.  I was advised that he felt that his brother just wanted to work and not go to school, but he added that his family is telling him that they have not had contact with him - other than Restricted phone calls once every 15 days or so.  It should be noted that the complainant did speak with Baltazar approximately 20 days after he left home but reportedly did not provide him with much information.  Since the case started, the reported contact Baltazar has had with the family has all been via restricted phone calls.  I requested that the complainant reach out to family in the US and Guatemala to see if Baltazar has contacted them.  Baltazar came to the U.S. on approximately January 22, 2022.  

      On June 2, 2023, I was notified by the complainant that his father (who lives in Guatemala) received a call from 443-484-6042 yesterday.  According to the brother/complainant, his father told him that it was Baltazar who called.  

      On June 2, 2023, at approximately 02:45 PM, I made contact with T-Mobile/Metro PCS and spoke with Kari.  I advised them on the facts of the case, and they advised they could provide pings for the phone number.  I was advised that these would be good for 48 hours and that I did not need to provide any further legal documents besides the request form.  At 03:03 P.M., I sent T-Mobile the completed form.

      On June 2, 2023, at approximately 03:19 P.M., I received the first ping "Location of 4434846042  at 6/2/2023 12:19:17 PM Pacific Daylight Time === Result === Lat, Long: 39.075612,-77.228394 Uncertainty: 1281m https://maps.google.com/maps?q=39.075612,-77.228394"  The center of the radius appears to be a quarry - 13900 Piney Meetinghouse Road, Rockville, Maryland 20850.  




      On June 2, 2023, at approximately 03:38 P.M., I contacted the Child Recovery Unit - Sgt. Flory.  It was determined that this case did not meet the criteria for an Amber Alert; however, information would be put out on social media.

      On June 2, 2023, at approximately 05:00 P.M., I made contact with the MSP Rockville Barrack due to the pings consistently coming back to the above location.  I requested that they attempt to contact someone at the quarry to conduct a precautionary check of the location and see if Baltazar possibly works at that location.  It should be noted I attempted to call the facility several times; however, the phone only rang.   

      Once new updates become available, they will be captured in future supplements.



Case OPEN.

List of Attachments:

    - None



Narrative:

      Since the last update, the ping that was attempted yielded negative results.  The radius of the pings was substantial in most cases; however, some small radius pings were returned.  A review of the data indicates that the phone is in the possession of someone other than the missing juvenile.  The MSP Child Recovery Unit was notified about this information.  It should be noted that the phone was called, and a female answered, but as soon as I identified myself, the subject hung up the phone.  It should be noted that investigative sites indicate that the phone is owned by an African American female who resides in Baltimore City (MD), where most of the pings came back when the phone appeared to be stationary.  

      At the time of this supplement, no known leads exist in this investigation.



Case to remain OPEN.

IncidentSuppNarrative.NarrativeTitle: Facial Recognition Request / Bulletin to Allied Agencies
IncidentSuppNarrative.NarrativeText:
List of Attachments:

    - None



Narrative:

      On July 10, 2023, I, Cpl. Theodore Buck of the Maryland State Police Criminal Enforcement Division contacted the Maryland Coordination and Analysis Center (MCAC) to see if a picture of the Juvenile could be entered into any facial recognition system available.  I also inquired about preparing a Law Enforcement bulletin on the juvenile for Maryland and the surrounding states.  I learned that there are no facial recognition programs that could run the photograph to try and locate the subject.  I was told it would only check booking photographs and other sources - for identification purposes.  In reference to the bulletin, MCAC advised they would send me a template to use, and once completed, they could send it to allied agencies.     

      On July 11, 2023, I sent MCAC a bulletin for dissemination to allied agencies.  Additionally, I attempted to contact the 443-484-6042 that Baltazar reportedly used; however, no contact was able to be made.  



Case OPEN.

ATTACHMENTS:
    Cleared NCIC Entry

NARRATIVE:
    On July 15, 2023 I was contacted by Corporal Buck. Corporal Buck advised the missing juvenile in this case was expected to return home at approximately 1500 hours, and request I verify he returned and complete an exit interview.

    On July 15, 2023 at approximately 1530 hours, Senior Trooper Horner and I responded to 1209 Liberty Road, Apartment 219, Sykesville, Carroll County, MD. Upon our arrival, we made contact with a juvenile female who opened the door and invited us inside the residence. Once inside the home, we made contact with an adult female and observed 4 additional juveniles in the home. One female juvenile spoke English and I asked if Baltazar or Sebastian were home. She stated Baltazar left for a minute, and someone would go get him. One of the other occupants left the residence to walk down the hall and returned shortly after with a male I recognized by the photos attached to this report as the missing juvenile. The female also advised she contacted Sebastian to return home due to him working nearby.

    I initiated a language line phone call due to the occupants having a language barrier. Corporal Buck was also added to the conference call. The juvenile male identified himself as Baltazar Chavez (DOB: 09-01-2007). He stated he had been in Virginia the last few months working, and had recently been staying with his sister. He would not provide her address. He denied being hurt/harmed or forced to work. Sebastian stated he reported Baltazar missing when he ran away from the home after not attending school and choosing to work instead. Sebastian explained the juvenile left due to Sebastian telling him he was required to go to school rather than working due to his age. Sebastian and Baltazar have reached an understanding that with Sebastian's permission Baltazar will reside with his sister. Baltazar agreed to maintain contact with Sebastian and Sebastian has confirmed that he has a good contact number for both Baltazar and their sister and would be able to make contact with them if needed. 

    Corporal Buck explained the importance of Baltazar attending school and that it would be in his best interest to do so. Sebastian was previously provided with Corporal Buck's phone number and Corporal Buck asked that the number also be shared with Baltazar and their sister should they have any concerns or need any assistance.

    Baltazar Chavez was removed from NCIC due to returning home under the care of his guardian. This concludes my involvement with this case.

CASE CLOSED
